  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For we are in danger to be called in question for this day’s uproar",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The A. V. seems here to be incorrect. ‘The word for “uproar” ought not to be joined with “this day.” The construction is contrary to N. T. usage, and the adoption of it has caused some violence to be done to the other words. The verb rendered “called in question” is the verb used in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 19:38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in the sense of “accuse,” while the word for “uproar” means “riot,” “sedition.” So the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Rev. Ver.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " gives, as an alternative version, “For indeed we are in danger to be accused of riot concerning this day.” Of course the town-clerk did not want himself to call it ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "riot",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but he intimates to them that other people may do so. He only styles it a “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "concourse",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
